%T A393836 36382573326
%N A393836 Number of fixed polygiraffes with n cells.
%C A393836 A giraffe is a (1,4)-leaper. A polygiraffe is a set of squares in the 2-dimensional grid, connected by giraffe leaps. As usual, fixed means that we only identify forms that are translations of each other; for one-sided forms (A393837), translations and rotations are identified; for free forms (A393838), translations, rotations, and reflections are identified.
%C A393836 The first 9 terms agree with A093877 and A151830. See formula in A393390.
%H A393836 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Giraffe_(chess)">Giraffe</a>.
%Y A393836 Row 4 of A393390.
%Y A393836 Cf. A030444 (polyknights), A093877 (polyzebras), A151830, A393837 (one-sided), A393838 (free), A393839.
